97
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:41,749
Scott: The thing is, I've realized this problem in gaming and technology, and I'm sure it also exists in other areas, right?

98
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:42,830
Scott: But consider this.

99
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:44,567
Scott: If I read a restaurant review, right?

100
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:50,384
Scott: That sounds pretty good to me, but I bet, I bet there are chefs out there who are like, "That restaurant critic doesn't know

101
00:03:50,425 --> 00:03:50,627
Scott: shit.".

102
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:52,228
