346
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:10,490
Scott: Well, I'm just saying, what's interesting about this story is not that somebody owned Chrome, even though that's kind of rare.

347
00:18:11,050 --> 00:18:16,770
Scott: It's that usually when someone discovers a vulnerability, they announce it in sort of different ways.

348
00:18:17,090 --> 00:18:21,910
Scott: There's the one where they just announce it to the world, and it's like, aha, you got to fix it now before everyone starts hacking you.

349
00:18:22,450 --> 00:18:27,330
Scott: Sometimes they're like, they whisper it to the company in question so that they can fix it and release a patch.

350
00:18:27,470 --> 00:18:30,589
Scott: And then when the patch comes out, then they announce it on the same day as the patch comes out.

351
00:18:31,292 --> 00:18:37,450
