00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:15,302
Rym: But how so?

385
00:20:15,422 --> 00:20:17,590
Rym: I'm I'm basically threatening telling the truth.

386
00:20:17,670 --> 00:20:18,894
Scott: You're threatening somebody.

387
00:20:19,095 --> 00:20:21,623
Scott: But it's not that telling the truth is always OK.

388
00:20:21,703 --> 00:20:22,847
Scott: It's threatening someone.

389
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:23,509
Scott: that's not OK.

390
00:20:24,070 --> 00:20:25,875
Rym: So what if I don't actually threaten?

391
00:20:26,356 --> 00:20:28,362
Rym: What if I simply say I found this vulnerability.

392
00:20:28,382 --> 00:20:31,390
Rym: I plan to tell the public in a week.

393
00:20:32,112 --> 00:20:32,616
Scott: You can do that.

394
00:20:32,636 --> 00:20:34,147
Rym: Dot, dot, dot.

395
00:20:35,910 --> 00:20:36,372
Rym: Hmm.

396
00:20:36,913 --> 00:20:39,924
Rym: Unless, you know, someone gave me something.

397
00:20:39,984 --> 00:20:40,666
Scott: Well, there you go.

398
00:20:40,686 --> 00:20:41,710
Scott: You crossed the line again, didn't you?

399
00:20:41,830 --> 00:20:42,473
Rym: So that's the line?

400
00:20:42,493 --> 00:20:43,196
Scott: Yeah, I think so.

401
00:20:43,357 --> 00:20:43,779
Rym: So I can't.

402
00:20:44,221 --> 00:20:45,627
Rym: What if I ask for a finder's fee?

403
00:20:45,647 --> 00:20:46,270
Rym: I don't even blackmail.

404
00:20:46,430 --> 00:20:48,939
Rym: I just say, would you be willing to pay me for the fact that I found this?

405
00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:51,950
Scott: Well, I think there might already be a bounty or something.

406
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:52,834
Rym: Without threatening.

407
00:20:52,874 --> 00:20:55,045
Rym: Just saying, will you pay me for the fact that I found this?

408
00:20:55,125 --> 00:20:55,789
Scott: You can ask.

409
00:20:55,849 --> 00:20:56,070
Scott: Sure.

410
00:20:56,430 --> 00:21:00,650
Rym: And then if they don't respond or say no, if you just happen to release to the public.

411
00:21:01,711 --> 00:21:02,515
Rym: The thing you found.

412
00:21:02,535 --> 00:21:03,800
Scott: I mean, you're not threatening them.

413
00:21:03,820 --> 00:21:05,969
Rym: Ah, so implied threats are OK.

414
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:09,250
Scott: It's not an implied threat if you're either threatening them or you're not.

415
00:21:10,550 --> 00:21:14,750
Rym: So as long as I don't actually directly threaten them, it's OK to blackmail the ever living fuck out of them.

416
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:16,720
Scott: You're not blackmailing them if you're not threatening them.

417
00:21:17,504 --> 00:21:18,750
Scott: Threat is part of blackmail.

418
00:21:19,310 --> 00:21:22,480
Rym: I sent someone the naked pictures I got of them and I'm like, hey, I found these pictures.

419
00:21:23,624 --> 00:21:25,310
Rym: I'm thinking about just publishing them, you know.

420
00:21:27,952 --> 00:21:28,234
Scott: All right.

421
00:21:28,274 --> 00:21:30,569
Rym: Would you be willing to pay me for the pictures?

422
00:21:33,112 --> 00:21:33,495
Scott: I don't know.

423
00:21:33,595 --> 00:21:34,823
Rym: At what point did I make a threat?

424
00:21:35,327 --> 00:21:35,669
Scott: I don't know.

425
00:21:36,490 --> 00:21:37,374
Scott: The point is, I don't.

426
00:21:37,795 --> 00:21:41,670
Scott: I think there is a definite line where if you threaten someone, that is no good now.

427
00:21:41,930 --> 00:21:43,293
Rym: I mean, my ethics are pretty simple.

428
00:21:43,353 --> 00:21:51,913
Rym: My personal ethical analysis is that if I find a severe vulnerability in software that is publicly available, I would inform the company.

429
00:21:52,395 --> 00:21:57,850
Rym: But if they did not respond or take me seriously or agree to fix it in a reasonable span, I would announce it publicly.

430
00:21:58,370 --> 00:21:58,992
Scott: That's a good idea.

